# .dockerignore — trims the build context sent to the container engine.
#
# IMPORTANT: this does NOT shrink the image. Image size is dominated by
# vista-m/Packages (~6.1 GB of FOIA routines + globals) which the Dockerfile
# COPYs and VistA needs — inherent to Strategy A. What this removes is
# build-context bloat (notably the ~934 MB .git, which now carries the VistA-M
# submodule's object store) and files the build never uses, so each `build`
# ships far less data to the engine. To actually shrink the image, subset the
# VistA-M packages (a separate follow-up).

# Git metadata — not needed by the build; .git holds the submodule object store.
.git
.gitmodules
.gitattributes
**/.git
**/.gitattributes

# Project docs & meta — not COPYed into the image.
docs/
*.md
README*

# Local build / orchestration files — not COPYed into the image.
Makefile
docker-compose.yml

# OS / editor cruft.
**/.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
